<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="669" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24557H/1–1647: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Norway</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">u. s. urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-18T09:00:00-05:00">January
                                    18, 1947—9 a. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>26. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 30 Jan 16.<note n="1" xml:id="d669fn1">Not printed.</note> As previously indicated we are
                            interested <gloss target="#t_SPITS1">Spits</gloss> question as party
                            1920 Treaty and because of general security considerations. We desire to
                            be kept informed and expect any agreement between Norway and Soviet
                            Union concerning <gloss target="#t_SPITS1">Spits</gloss> will be subject
                            approval other signatories. Last week’s communiqué Norwegian <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> apparently satisfactory on these
                            points and no action on our part seems necessary at this time.</p>
                        <p>Brit Emb Wash has been in touch with Dept and has been informed along
                            above lines.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Oslo as 26, repeated Moscow as 85 and London as 297.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>